vulnerability.name: USN-6488-2
vulnerability.description: USN-6488-1 fixed a vulnerability in strongSwan. This update provides the corresponding updates for Ubuntu 16.04 LTS and Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.  Original advisory details:   Florian Picca discovered that strongSwan incorrectly handled certain DH  public values. A remote attacker could use this issue to cause strongSwan  to crash, resulting in a denial of service, or possibly execute arbitrary  code.

statements.status_notes: strongSwan could be made to crash or run programs if it received specially crafted network traffic. Available with Ubuntu Pro.
